verses.text:
Pray, he is there;
Speak, he is list&rsquo;ning.
You are his child;
His love now surrounds you.
He hears your prayer;
He loves the children.
Of such is the kingdom, the kingdom of heav&rsquo;n.

I begin by saying &ldquo;Dear Heavenly Father&rdquo;;
I thank him for blessings he sends;
Then humbly I ask him for things that I need,
In the name of Jesus Christ, Amen.

Thank thee for the world so sweet;
Thank thee for the food we eat;
Thank thee for the birds that sing;
Thank thee, God, for ev&rsquo;rything!

Have a most exciting Christmas!
Ring a bell and trim a tree;
Stuff a stocking for a loved one;
Hang the holly joyously.

Have a happy fam’ly Christmas!
Gather all your loved ones near;
Talk about the baby Jesus;
Wrap your hearts in love this year.

As I read the scriptures daily&mdash;
Words of Christ, the Holy One&mdash;
In my heart I&rsquo;ll hear God tell me:

Samuel was a prophet chosen as a boy.
Hannah promised God her son would serve with joy.
In the tabernacle, Samuel heard his name;
He was called by God and answered, &ldquo;Here I am!&rdquo;

We believe that the first principles and ordinances of the Gospel
are:&nbsp;first, Faith in the Lord Jesus Christ;
second, Repentance;
third, Baptism by immersion for the remission of sins;
fourth, Laying on of hands for the gift of the Holy Ghost.

We believe in the literal gathering of Israel
and in the restoration of the Ten Tribes;
that Zion (the New Jerusalem) will be built upon
the American continent;
that Christ will reign personally upon the earth;
and that the earth will be renewed
and receive its paradisiacal glory.

Latter-day prophets are: number one,
Joseph Smith; then Brigham Young;
John Taylor came third, we know;
Then Wilford Woodruff; Lorenzo Snow;
Joseph F. Smith (remember the <em>F</em>);
Heber J. Grant; and George Albert Smith;
David O. McKay was followed by Joseph Fielding Smith,
Then Harold B. Lee, Spencer W. Kimball,
Ezra Taft Benson, Howard W. Hunter.
*Gordon B. Hinckley shows the way.
We hear and follow his words today.

A shining star, shining brightly,
Not so very far, shining brightly;
Be a shining star. Shine so brightly;
Shine right where you are, brightly!

Dare, dare, dare to do right;
Dare, dare, dare to be true,
Dare to be true, dare to be true.

Dare, dare, dare to do right;
Dare, dare, dare to be true,
Dare to be true, dare to be true.

There’s a right way to live and be happy;
It is choosing the right ev’ry day.
I am learning the teachings of Jesus;
They will help me and show me the way.

Onward, ever onward, as we glory in his name;
Onward, ever onward, as we glory in his name;
Forward, pressing forward, as a triumph song we sing.
God our strength will be; press forward ever,
Called to serve our King.

Called to know the richness of his blessing&mdash;
Sons and daughters, children of a King&mdash;
Glad of heart, his holy name confessing,
Praises unto him we bring.

Onward, ever onward, as we glory in his name;
Onward, ever onward, as we glory in his name;
Forward, pressing forward, as a triumph song we sing.
God our strength will be; press forward ever,
Called to serve our King.

How dear to God are little children;
With him their spirit life began.
So priceless their security,
Their innocence and purity;
They are a part of his eternal plan.

I&rsquo;ll try to be good;
I&rsquo;ll do as I should.
I&rsquo;ll whisper, &ldquo;I love you too.&rdquo;
I wish ev&rsquo;ry child in the whole wide world
Had a grandmother* just like you.

The father of our home leads our family
With wisdom’s light in all that’s right;
My father’s good to me.

The father of our ward tends with loving care
Each member’s needs with kindly deeds;
Our bishop’s always there.

In the leafy treetops, the birds sing &ldquo;Good morning.&rdquo;
They&rsquo;re first to see the sun.
They must tell ev&rsquo;ryone.
In the leafy treetops, the birds sing &ldquo;Good morning.&rdquo;

Little purple pansies, touched with yellow gold,
Growing in one corner of the garden old;
We are very tiny but must try, try, try

①&nbsp;Sing, sing, sing;
②&nbsp;I like to sing.
③&nbsp;I like to sing a song;
④&nbsp;Sing, sing, sing!

Here we are together,* together, together;
Oh, here we are together in our family.&dagger;
There&rsquo;s <em>(name)</em> and <em>(name)</em> and <em>(name)</em> and <em>(name);</em>
Oh, here we are together this bright, sunny day.&dagger;

Do as I&rsquo;m doing;
Follow, follow me!
Do as I&rsquo;m doing;
Follow, follow me!
If I do it high or low,
If I do it fast or slow,
Do as I&rsquo;m doing;
Follow, follow me!
Do as I&rsquo;m doing;
Follow, follow me!
